      "content": "i see. so the \"move fast\" crowd basically wants to gamble with survival just for the sake of speed? it feels like their side isn't really addressing the actual danger, just complaining about the rules. is there any legitimate scientific basis for them thinking they can outrun the risk, or is it just a matter of wanting more profit/innovation?",
